HEADWORD: Thurrok
<hw>Thur"rok</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>⟦thorn⟧urruc</ets> a boat.]</ety> <def>The hold of a ship; a
sink.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Small drops of water that enter through a little crevice into the
<qex>thurrok</qex> and into the bottom of a ship.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thursday</ent>⟦br⟧
